1
00:00:05,280 --> 00:00:06,980
(Episode 6)

2
00:00:13,390 --> 00:00:14,550
Come with me for now.

3
00:00:37,740 --> 00:00:40,310
Bo A, someone keeps texting you.

4
00:00:40,510 --> 00:00:41,680
It's from Oh Hui Kyeong.

5
00:00:42,910 --> 00:00:44,320
She's a friend
who recently got married...

6
00:00:44,320 --> 00:00:45,650
and went to Australia
for her honeymoon.

7
00:00:45,650 --> 00:00:46,790
Can you excuse me?

8
00:00:47,290 --> 00:00:48,390
I'll take that.

9
00:00:50,990 --> 00:00:53,020
Bo A, I'm in Melbourne.

10
00:00:53,020 --> 00:00:55,030
Isn't this Seo Jae Uk,
the one working as a welder?

11
00:01:16,180 --> 00:01:17,750
I'll get going, then.

12
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:21,190
Oh, no.

13
00:01:35,230 --> 00:01:36,400
What's going on?

14
00:01:42,470 --> 00:01:43,640
Check the text you got.

15
00:01:48,610 --> 00:01:49,710
I'm sorry.

16
00:01:50,050 --> 00:01:51,380
I have to go to him.

17
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:54,220
I just found out where he is.

18
00:01:55,650 --> 00:01:57,920
I'm sorry, Ji Hyuk.

19
00:02:15,610 --> 00:02:17,810
Honey, something must be up.

20
00:02:18,210 --> 00:02:19,940
Where are the bride's parents going?

21
00:02:20,610 --> 00:02:21,680
Is Bo A sick?

22
00:02:22,110 --> 00:02:24,280
Su Bin, get me Ji Wan.

23
00:02:24,820 --> 00:02:25,820
Don't just sit there,

24
00:02:25,820 --> 00:02:27,890
and find out what's going on.

25
00:02:27,890 --> 00:02:29,090
All right.

26
00:02:29,390 --> 00:02:31,890
We must apologize to the guests...

27
00:02:31,890 --> 00:02:33,560
who attended the wedding today.

28
00:02:34,260 --> 00:02:35,690
It has been canceled...

29
00:02:35,690 --> 00:02:38,030
due to personal reasons.

30
00:02:43,900 --> 00:02:46,370
What on earth am I hearing?

31
00:03:03,420 --> 00:03:06,090
CEO Jung Ho Yeong
extends his apologies.

32
00:03:06,930 --> 00:03:09,560
You should head home right away.

33
00:03:09,990 --> 00:03:12,800
You should at least tell us
what happened to the bride.

34
00:03:13,230 --> 00:03:16,000
The wedding certainly
can't continue at this point,

35
00:03:16,630 --> 00:03:18,700
but he'll let you know
the reason later.

36
00:03:18,700 --> 00:03:19,770
Look here.

37
00:03:19,770 --> 00:03:22,110
What are we going
to tell our guests?

38
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:28,150
Just say it concerns
the bride's health.

39
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:32,120
But...

40
00:03:32,920 --> 00:03:34,790
What on earth is going on?

41
00:03:34,790 --> 00:03:36,190
Is the bride sick?

42
00:03:36,190 --> 00:03:38,190
Or are we supposed to lie
that she's sick?

43
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:40,760
Su Bin.

44
00:03:42,030 --> 00:03:43,530
Take Ji Hyuk's car...

45
00:03:43,530 --> 00:03:45,400
and drive Mom, Dad,
and Grandma home.

46
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:46,800
We should hear from Ji Hyuk first.

47
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:47,830
What happened to Bo A?

48
00:03:47,830 --> 00:03:50,400
Look, the bride ran away.

49
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:51,800
What?

50
00:03:51,900 --> 00:03:53,770
What are you two whispering about?

51
00:03:53,770 --> 00:03:54,940
Let me in on it.

52
00:03:55,610 --> 00:03:56,670
It's nothing, Grandma.

53
00:03:57,510 --> 00:03:59,680
So, get the others home quickly.

54
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:01,510
Don't let them be humiliated here.

55
00:04:01,580 --> 00:04:03,410
I need to clean up this mess
with Seong Jae.

56
00:04:03,410 --> 00:04:04,420
I'll see you later.

57
00:04:04,420 --> 00:04:06,080
- Got it.
- What was that?

58
00:04:06,250 --> 00:04:07,290
Grandma.

59
00:04:08,290 --> 00:04:09,390
- Mom, Dad.
- Yes?

60
00:04:10,390 --> 00:04:11,490
Let's go home.

61
00:04:11,590 --> 00:04:13,120
How can we leave like this?

62
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:14,260
We should get some answers first.

63
00:04:14,260 --> 00:04:16,190
We need to hurry home for now.
Please, Mom. Dad.

64
00:04:16,190 --> 00:04:18,100
We should know what's going on.

65
00:04:18,100 --> 00:04:19,660
Get Ji Hyuk over here.

66
00:04:19,660 --> 00:04:20,670
He's not here.

67
00:04:20,670 --> 00:04:22,030
I'll tell you why
on the way home, Dad.

68
00:04:22,030 --> 00:04:23,030
Please.

69
00:04:23,030 --> 00:04:24,570
Let's find out
what's going on first.

70
00:04:24,740 --> 00:04:27,270
Let's go home, Dad.
Please? Let's go.

71
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:32,610
- What's going on?
- The bride ran away.

72
00:04:32,610 --> 00:04:34,210
- What?
- The bride ran away?

73
00:04:34,210 --> 00:04:35,780
- I heard people chatting outside.
- Okay.

74
00:04:35,780 --> 00:04:37,850
She went to her ex-boyfriend.

75
00:04:37,850 --> 00:04:39,620
Oh, dear.

76
00:04:39,980 --> 00:04:42,720
- Tell me about it.
- It's shameful for both families.

77
00:04:45,790 --> 00:04:47,760
Try calling him. Go on.

78
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:49,530
What on earth is going on?

79
00:04:49,530 --> 00:04:51,130
- Poor Ji Hyuk.
- This is awful.

80
00:04:51,130 --> 00:04:52,300
Isn't he picking up?

81
00:04:53,830 --> 00:04:54,970
Guests,

82
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:57,370
the food has already been prepared,

83
00:04:57,370 --> 00:04:58,970
so please stay and enjoy your meal.

84
00:05:04,040 --> 00:05:06,010
Are you kidding me?

85
00:05:12,050 --> 00:05:13,890
What's going on?

86
00:05:21,430 --> 00:05:22,890
Get some rest here.

87
00:05:25,730 --> 00:05:27,130
I'll go back and clean things up.

88
00:05:44,180 --> 00:05:45,850
Unbelievable.

89
00:05:46,620 --> 00:05:48,620
Did the bride run away?

90
00:05:51,290 --> 00:05:52,820
It serves you right, Lee Ji Hyuk.

91
00:05:53,260 --> 00:05:54,690
I knew it.

92
00:06:10,140 --> 00:06:11,140
Loser.

93
00:06:13,710 --> 00:06:16,510
Unbelievable.
Can this be more annoying?

94
00:06:22,550 --> 00:06:25,020
Su Bin, tell us what's going on.

95
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:27,290
What happened today?

96
00:06:28,090 --> 00:06:29,090
Well...

97
00:06:29,290 --> 00:06:31,800
Su Bin, tell us what you know
right now.

98
00:06:35,230 --> 00:06:37,840
Bo A must've been seeing
another guy.

99
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:40,540
What?

100
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:42,410
"Ji Hyuk, I'm sorry."

101
00:06:42,410 --> 00:06:43,570
"I have to go to him."

102
00:06:43,570 --> 00:06:45,080
She sent a text like that.

103
00:06:45,510 --> 00:06:46,780
To Ji Hyuk's phone.

104
00:06:46,940 --> 00:06:48,310
Who is she going to?

105
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:51,580
I don't understand
a word you just said.

106
00:06:52,450 --> 00:06:54,390
It doesn't seem like
she and Ji Hyuk dated.

107
00:06:54,420 --> 00:06:56,590
Was he marrying a girl
he wasn't even dating?

108
00:06:57,490 --> 00:06:58,860
Why?

109
00:07:01,930 --> 00:07:03,190
(My eldest son)

110
00:07:04,430 --> 00:07:07,770
The receiver can't come
to the phone right now.

111
00:07:07,770 --> 00:07:09,400
Please call again.

112
00:07:53,910 --> 00:07:56,150
- You're here.
- Yes, good to see you.

113
00:07:56,150 --> 00:07:57,250
Yes, that's right.

114
00:07:57,650 --> 00:07:59,320
Thank you!

115
00:08:00,850 --> 00:08:03,650
After the wedding,
there will be a party...

116
00:08:03,650 --> 00:08:05,520
for the former and current members
of Value of Hangyeol.

117
00:08:06,590 --> 00:08:08,860
- No, not like that.
- Come on.

118
00:08:08,860 --> 00:08:10,800
- Come here, then.
- Hey, seriously...

119
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:11,860
Eun Oh, you're here.

120
00:08:11,860 --> 00:08:13,300
- Hey.
- Hi, Eun Oh.

121
00:08:13,300 --> 00:08:15,070
How did you get in here?

122
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:16,970
Su Jeong gave us
the lock combination.

123
00:08:16,970 --> 00:08:18,140
- That's right.
- I see.

124
00:08:18,140 --> 00:08:19,170
Hey, Eun Oh.

125
00:08:19,170 --> 00:08:22,010
- How many tables should we set up?
- Well...

126
00:08:22,010 --> 00:08:23,510
Six will do.

127
00:08:23,510 --> 00:08:25,140
Why did you get here so fast?

128
00:08:25,140 --> 00:08:26,610
- Bring that here.
- Hey!

129
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:31,920
- Hello.
- Hi.

130
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:33,280
- Have you been well?
- Hi.

131
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:35,020
- It's been a while.
- It's good to see you.

132
00:08:35,020 --> 00:08:36,220
Hello.

133
00:08:36,220 --> 00:08:37,890
- Just a second.
- I got this.

134
00:08:37,920 --> 00:08:39,360
- Come to the front, please.
- You made it.

135
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:40,460
- Hey.
- Hey.

136
00:08:40,830 --> 00:08:41,890
I see you prepared quite the party.

137
00:08:41,890 --> 00:08:44,130
It only takes a few seconds
for 20-somethings.

138
00:08:44,130 --> 00:08:46,100
- Should we sit there?
- Sounds good.

139
00:08:46,100 --> 00:08:47,270
- No way.
- You made it.

140
00:08:47,270 --> 00:08:48,270
- Hello!
- Wait.

141
00:08:48,270 --> 00:08:49,270
- Please sit over here.
- Yes?

142
00:08:49,270 --> 00:08:50,300
Hyeon Su.

143
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:53,570
Do you think
we can be doing this today?

144
00:08:54,640 --> 00:08:56,540
Then do you want
to throw all this away?

145
00:08:56,940 --> 00:08:57,940
Well...

146
00:08:58,540 --> 00:09:02,080
I don't think this is the time
for us to wine and dine here.

147
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:04,480
This is why we like you, Eun Oh.

148
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:06,280
No one hates you, you know?

149
00:09:07,490 --> 00:09:08,490
What?

150
00:09:09,050 --> 00:09:10,050
You know what?

151
00:09:11,060 --> 00:09:12,760
When someone
experiences a misfortune,

152
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:14,860
not everyone needs to worry.

153
00:09:15,590 --> 00:09:17,300
And people
won't just worry about it.

154
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:21,000
Sometimes,
curiosity can surpass worry.

155
00:09:22,900 --> 00:09:25,670
I'm not sure
what you're talking about.

156
00:09:25,970 --> 00:09:27,810
I mean,
that's what life is all about.

157
00:09:28,070 --> 00:09:29,210
It's no big deal.

158
00:09:31,340 --> 00:09:34,050
- But how...
- The thing is...

159
00:09:34,810 --> 00:09:36,550
- Hello.
- Hello.

160
00:09:36,680 --> 00:09:38,580
- Hello.
- Please have a seat here.

161
00:09:40,050 --> 00:09:41,120
Have a seat.

162
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:01,210
(Jung Bo A)

163
00:10:01,210 --> 00:10:02,440
(I just found out where he is.)

164
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:03,670
(I'm sorry, Ji Hyuk.)

165
00:10:20,260 --> 00:10:21,730
This is really good.

166
00:10:22,930 --> 00:10:24,660
Eun Oh, have a seat.

167
00:10:24,660 --> 00:10:27,100
Right. Let's drink. Come here.

168
00:10:27,260 --> 00:10:29,270
I'm the manager here. I should work.

169
00:10:31,670 --> 00:10:34,870
Maybe Jung Bo A's father
gave him money or something.

170
00:10:34,970 --> 00:10:36,270
About a year ago,

171
00:10:36,270 --> 00:10:38,340
the man vanished without a trace,

172
00:10:38,340 --> 00:10:39,840
so Jung Bo A gave up on him.

173
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:43,580
In the meantime,
her father pushed for the marriage.

174
00:10:43,580 --> 00:10:45,820
Eun Oh, you must know.

175
00:10:46,180 --> 00:10:48,290
How did Ji Hyuk and Bo A
end up together?

176
00:10:49,520 --> 00:10:50,520
I don't know.

177
00:10:51,190 --> 00:10:52,560
- Su Jeong.
- What?

178
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:56,090
By the way, how do you all know...

179
00:10:56,090 --> 00:10:58,060
about Ji Hyuk's runaway bride?

180
00:10:58,260 --> 00:10:59,300
Well...

181
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:01,900
Back in college, we renovated...

182
00:11:01,900 --> 00:11:04,700
Edel Orphanage,
the largest orphanage in Cheongpo.

183
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:07,100
It was a huge project
involving six universities in Seoul.

184
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:09,410
Back then,
Bo A and a guy from the orphanage...

185
00:11:09,410 --> 00:11:11,110
fell in love,
which caused quite a stir.

186
00:11:11,980 --> 00:11:14,310
So, does that mean
Ji Hyuk and Bo A...

187
00:11:14,310 --> 00:11:16,780
kept in touch after that?

188
00:11:16,880 --> 00:11:17,950
I don't know.

189
00:11:18,050 --> 00:11:19,850
You know, Ji Hyuk isn't the type...

190
00:11:19,850 --> 00:11:21,620
- to talk about his personal life.
- That's true.

191
00:11:22,090 --> 00:11:23,690
What is Ji Hyuk doing?

192
00:11:24,490 --> 00:11:26,890
- Call him.
- He's not answering.

193
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:39,940
The bride had acute appendicitis.
It couldn't be helped.

194
00:11:41,710 --> 00:11:42,810
Hey, I have to go.

195
00:11:44,440 --> 00:11:45,510
Ji Hyuk.

196
00:11:45,880 --> 00:11:47,040
What do you think you're doing?

197
00:11:47,450 --> 00:11:49,480
How could you
mess things up like this?

198
00:11:50,350 --> 00:11:52,320
Mom and Dad are calling the guests
to apologize...

199
00:11:52,320 --> 00:11:53,350
and return the cash gifts.

200
00:11:59,860 --> 00:12:00,860
I'm sorry.

201
00:12:02,730 --> 00:12:04,500
Yes. I'm sorry.

202
00:12:05,260 --> 00:12:07,630
Send me your bank account number.

203
00:12:08,830 --> 00:12:09,870
No.

204
00:12:10,130 --> 00:12:12,740
I don't know when he'll have
another wedding ceremony.

205
00:12:15,010 --> 00:12:16,270
Ji Hyuk is home.

206
00:12:16,870 --> 00:12:18,110
Send me a text.

207
00:12:22,910 --> 00:12:24,120
You fool!

208
00:12:26,220 --> 00:12:27,220
I'm sorry.

209
00:12:28,250 --> 00:12:31,060
I put you two
in such an awkward spot. I'm sorry.

210
00:12:31,560 --> 00:12:32,620
"Awkward?"

211
00:12:33,090 --> 00:12:34,530
Did you just say an awkward spot?

212
00:12:35,160 --> 00:12:38,560
Honey, let him explain
the whole story first.

213
00:12:40,300 --> 00:12:41,830
Sit, Ji Hyuk.

214
00:12:52,640 --> 00:12:53,710
Hey.

215
00:12:54,350 --> 00:12:57,450
Is it true that the bride went back
to her ex-boyfriend?

216
00:12:57,650 --> 00:12:58,850
Did you two never actually date?

217
00:13:00,950 --> 00:13:01,950
No.

218
00:13:02,250 --> 00:13:03,790
My goodness.

219
00:13:04,560 --> 00:13:05,990
Then...

220
00:13:06,560 --> 00:13:08,960
Then why did you decide
to marry her?

221
00:13:09,730 --> 00:13:12,030
We both needed this marriage.

222
00:13:14,060 --> 00:13:15,200
You needed it?

223
00:13:16,130 --> 00:13:17,130
What do you mean?

224
00:13:17,770 --> 00:13:20,470
I guess she tried to forget
her ex-boyfriend and move on.

225
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:22,870
What about you?
Why did you need her?

226
00:13:23,540 --> 00:13:24,880
Because she's the daughter
of Haneul Construction's CEO.

227
00:13:26,410 --> 00:13:29,410
What? Because she's the daughter
of Haneul Construction's CEO?

228
00:13:29,880 --> 00:13:30,950
My goodness.

229
00:13:31,380 --> 00:13:33,550
What's that supposed to mean?

230
00:13:34,050 --> 00:13:36,720
Are you saying
you wanted to marry her for money...

231
00:13:37,290 --> 00:13:39,290
because she came from a rich family,

232
00:13:39,520 --> 00:13:41,790
when you didn't even love her
or date her?

233
00:13:43,860 --> 00:13:46,800
I believe marriage is something
you do out of necessity.

234
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:48,430
That's what I believe.

235
00:13:49,030 --> 00:13:50,070
Ji Hyuk.

236
00:13:50,500 --> 00:13:52,000
You crazy fool!

237
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:55,770
He should just say sorry
and beg for forgiveness.

238
00:13:55,770 --> 00:13:57,140
Why is he being like this?

239
00:13:57,340 --> 00:13:58,580
My goodness.

240
00:13:58,710 --> 00:13:59,810
Is Ji Hyuk home?

241
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:02,410
How did things go
at the wedding hall?

242
00:14:02,450 --> 00:14:04,820
Seong Jae and I took care of it.

243
00:14:05,650 --> 00:14:08,520
You are not in your right mind.

244
00:14:09,490 --> 00:14:11,590
Do you even hear yourself?

245
00:14:11,990 --> 00:14:13,090
Are you out of your mind?

246
00:14:14,060 --> 00:14:17,260
How could you think of marrying
someone for money as a man?

247
00:14:19,030 --> 00:14:21,630
You always tell me about things
I shouldn't do as a man.

248
00:14:22,270 --> 00:14:23,830
But these days,
you don't have to be...

249
00:14:23,830 --> 00:14:25,370
the breadwinner
just because you're a man.

250
00:14:26,100 --> 00:14:27,540
Times have changed
since your generation.

251
00:14:28,510 --> 00:14:29,610
People in my generation...

252
00:14:30,110 --> 00:14:32,940
don't believe they have to marry
someone they love,

253
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:35,310
and they don't see marriage
as a necessity.

254
00:14:35,510 --> 00:14:37,180
You and your pathetic excuses again.

255
00:14:37,180 --> 00:14:38,880
Are you blaming the times again?

256
00:14:39,450 --> 00:14:41,220
Do you think things were easy
for my generation?

257
00:14:41,790 --> 00:14:42,790
We were a lot poorer...

258
00:14:42,790 --> 00:14:44,790
and had a harder time
than you do now.

259
00:14:45,790 --> 00:14:47,390
I wanted to live a good life.

260
00:14:49,690 --> 00:14:51,160
Growing old together
with someone I love?

261
00:14:51,760 --> 00:14:53,400
The role and sacrifice
of the head of the household?

262
00:14:54,570 --> 00:14:57,400
For someone like me, who grew up
struggling just to support myself,

263
00:14:57,800 --> 00:14:58,840
it sounds like
a story from a different world.

264
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:01,010
That's why
I didn't want to get married.

265
00:15:01,170 --> 00:15:03,170
If I were alone,
I could live a decent life.

266
00:15:04,280 --> 00:15:05,740
But then,
this opportunity came to me.

267
00:15:09,350 --> 00:15:10,680
That's why I made such a decision.

268
00:15:11,450 --> 00:15:13,580
What? So, are you...

269
00:15:14,590 --> 00:15:17,420
blaming us, your parents,
for not being born...

270
00:15:17,420 --> 00:15:18,560
with a silver spoon in your mouth?

271
00:15:18,590 --> 00:15:19,720
That's not what I meant!

272
00:15:19,790 --> 00:15:21,730
That's exactly what you are saying!

273
00:15:23,190 --> 00:15:25,830
Fine. You've got such a big head.

274
00:15:26,500 --> 00:15:28,970
So, did you try
to marry for money...

275
00:15:28,970 --> 00:15:30,670
just to raise your children
in an affluent family?

276
00:15:30,730 --> 00:15:32,600
Yes, I did.

277
00:15:33,300 --> 00:15:34,710
I didn't want to live a shabby life,

278
00:15:34,710 --> 00:15:36,740
and I didn't want my children
to grow up poor.

279
00:15:37,940 --> 00:15:39,380
I don't want to live a life...

280
00:15:40,410 --> 00:15:42,280
where I can't give my children
what they want,

281
00:15:42,280 --> 00:15:43,580
always worrying about rent...

282
00:15:43,580 --> 00:15:44,880
and their academy fees.

283
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:46,850
I don't want to live
constantly worrying about...

284
00:15:47,020 --> 00:15:48,490
when I'll get laid off from work.

285
00:15:48,490 --> 00:15:49,990
So that's what you're saying.

286
00:15:49,990 --> 00:15:51,520
You are blaming me now.

287
00:15:51,520 --> 00:15:54,390
I'm not blaming you.
That's just how my life has been.

288
00:15:57,030 --> 00:15:58,060
Yes.

289
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:00,630
I know you've done your best.

290
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:03,030
With your modest income,

291
00:16:03,470 --> 00:16:05,700
you had to support Grandfather
through his 20 years of illness.

292
00:16:07,070 --> 00:16:08,840
I know you worked really hard...

293
00:16:08,840 --> 00:16:11,640
to take care of Grandmother
with dementia and raise three kids.

294
00:16:13,110 --> 00:16:14,180
But you know what?

295
00:16:14,910 --> 00:16:16,250
I didn't want to live like that.

296
00:16:17,010 --> 00:16:18,220
That's how I felt.

297
00:16:21,520 --> 00:16:22,620
So don't ask me...

298
00:16:24,420 --> 00:16:26,520
why I'm not trying to live like you.

299
00:16:28,590 --> 00:16:29,590
You will...

300
00:16:31,300 --> 00:16:32,660
never understand my generation.

301
00:16:33,130 --> 00:16:35,300
Like me? Live like me?

302
00:16:36,270 --> 00:16:37,740
I didn't tell you to live like me!

303
00:16:38,140 --> 00:16:39,870
If you didn't want to live like me,

304
00:16:39,870 --> 00:16:41,540
you should've stayed single...

305
00:16:41,540 --> 00:16:43,240
like you always said!

306
00:16:43,610 --> 00:16:46,310
You shouldn't have sold yourself off
for money, you fool!

307
00:16:48,250 --> 00:16:50,980
Honey, that was a bit harsh.

308
00:16:51,050 --> 00:16:52,280
That's not harsh at all.

309
00:16:53,880 --> 00:16:55,020
What is the other excuse?

310
00:16:56,720 --> 00:16:57,790
Choice.

311
00:16:59,120 --> 00:17:00,120
What?

312
00:17:01,830 --> 00:17:02,890
It was my choice.

313
00:17:04,190 --> 00:17:05,630
Things didn't go well today,

314
00:17:06,130 --> 00:17:07,660
and I caused you a lot of trouble.

315
00:17:09,070 --> 00:17:11,370
For that, I'm truly sorry.
I really am.

316
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:14,410
But...

317
00:17:16,310 --> 00:17:18,240
if I had another chance like this,

318
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:21,950
I would make the same choice again.

319
00:17:25,480 --> 00:17:26,480
My gosh.

320
00:17:27,150 --> 00:17:28,290
Ji Hyuk.

321
00:17:29,290 --> 00:17:30,790
Why did you turn out like this?

322
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:33,520
I don't think
this is how I raised you.

323
00:17:34,220 --> 00:17:36,030
If you believe your life is right,

324
00:17:37,160 --> 00:17:38,230
then just keep believing it.

325
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:43,370
But don't force your children
to agree with you.

326
00:17:44,170 --> 00:17:46,540
What did you just say?

327
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:48,970
It's just that
our values are different.

328
00:17:50,670 --> 00:17:52,240
You're trapped
in old-fashioned thinking.

329
00:17:54,510 --> 00:17:55,880
So you two will never...

330
00:17:58,050 --> 00:17:59,320
understand my choice.

331
00:18:00,280 --> 00:18:03,450
You keep insisting
that you did the right thing!

332
00:18:03,920 --> 00:18:05,690
Ji Hyuk must be out of his mind.

333
00:18:06,360 --> 00:18:07,860
I understand how he feels.

334
00:18:07,930 --> 00:18:09,290
That's reality.

335
00:18:09,490 --> 00:18:10,490
What?

336
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:13,600
I also don't want to live
struggling to make ends meet.

337
00:18:14,130 --> 00:18:15,970
I want to live
with my head held high.

338
00:18:16,170 --> 00:18:18,170
Isn't it natural
that you want to enjoy a life...

339
00:18:18,170 --> 00:18:19,440
- that others envy?
- Hey.

340
00:18:19,540 --> 00:18:21,210
Ji Hyuk doesn't even seem
human to me.

341
00:18:21,210 --> 00:18:22,440
I'm really disappointed.

342
00:18:22,440 --> 00:18:24,210
Don't you think we, of all people,
should understand him?

343
00:18:24,580 --> 00:18:26,340
Ji Hyuk is the victim here.

344
00:18:26,740 --> 00:18:29,410
Why are you disappointed
when you didn't do anything for him?

345
00:18:30,580 --> 00:18:31,850
Do you not remember
when we were little?

346
00:18:32,150 --> 00:18:34,890
He gave us allowances
from his part-time job in college...

347
00:18:34,890 --> 00:18:36,520
and kept it up
even after he got a full-time job.

348
00:18:37,790 --> 00:18:39,990
I don't want to take his side
just because he gave me something.

349
00:18:39,990 --> 00:18:42,130
I mean, he turned the whole house
upside down.

350
00:18:50,570 --> 00:18:51,970
Do you have anything more to say?

351
00:18:54,170 --> 00:18:56,640
What more can I say?
It's just a waste of energy.

352
00:18:57,980 --> 00:19:01,880
My great son says
he has no regret at all...

353
00:19:02,810 --> 00:19:05,720
