00:30:48,750 --> 00:30:51,720
Can't you eat
for the sake of your son?

531
00:31:06,400 --> 00:31:07,770
It's been three days,

532
00:31:08,440 --> 00:31:09,910
but we haven't heard from him.

533
00:31:11,170 --> 00:31:14,040
Don't even bother caring whether
he's dead or alive somewhere.

534
00:31:15,950 --> 00:31:17,780
He's my eldest grandson!

535
00:31:18,920 --> 00:31:21,780
I don't care how angry you are.
How dare you be that cruel?

536
00:31:22,190 --> 00:31:23,190
Mother.

537
00:31:23,420 --> 00:31:26,260
As of today,
Ji Wan is your eldest grandson.

538
00:31:29,260 --> 00:31:31,030
This wasn't supposed to happen,

539
00:31:31,030 --> 00:31:32,700
nor should it have.

540
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:34,700
He walked out thinking
he'd made the right decision,

541
00:31:34,960 --> 00:31:37,130
and I don't plan
on letting him back in.

542
00:31:37,970 --> 00:31:40,540
So don't worry yourself
over this, Mother.

543
00:31:41,000 --> 00:31:43,410
Da Jeong and you two.
Go about your lives.

544
00:31:44,110 --> 00:31:46,810
Don't worry about something
that's not worth our concern.

545
00:31:47,940 --> 00:31:49,050
Let's eat, Mother.

546
00:32:09,330 --> 00:32:11,830
(Cheongpo Motel)

547
00:32:12,700 --> 00:32:13,740
Look here!

548
00:32:14,340 --> 00:32:16,170
- Hey!
- See?

549
00:32:16,170 --> 00:32:17,670
I knew it.

550
00:32:17,740 --> 00:32:20,440
I think I smell something too.
Darn it.

551
00:32:20,610 --> 00:32:22,480
Open it already.

552
00:32:24,550 --> 00:32:25,720
My gosh!

553
00:32:26,050 --> 00:32:28,380
Thank all the deities I know!

554
00:32:28,520 --> 00:32:29,590
What's this about?

555
00:32:30,320 --> 00:32:31,920
Goodness me.

556
00:32:31,950 --> 00:32:33,520
He's fine.

557
00:32:33,820 --> 00:32:36,360
How can you go three days
without eating anything...

558
00:32:36,360 --> 00:32:37,960
or ordering food?

559
00:32:37,960 --> 00:32:39,830
I thought you had killed yourself!

560
00:32:39,830 --> 00:32:42,000
You shouldn't be doing this here.

561
00:32:42,700 --> 00:32:43,730
You thought I killed myself?

562
00:32:43,730 --> 00:32:45,670
Even now, I'm still worried.

563
00:32:45,670 --> 00:32:47,340
There's no light in his eyes,

564
00:32:47,340 --> 00:32:48,640
and he looks utterly defeated.

565
00:32:48,810 --> 00:32:49,970
I can't take this anymore.

566
00:32:50,370 --> 00:32:52,580
How can you not even order
a bowl of jjajangmyeon?

567
00:32:52,840 --> 00:32:53,880
Get out already!

568
00:32:55,210 --> 00:32:56,880
Didn't you say it's been three days?

569
00:32:57,010 --> 00:32:58,210
My goodness.

570
00:32:58,310 --> 00:33:00,050
He has no idea
how much time has passed.

571
00:33:00,950 --> 00:33:03,350
I'll refund you for the day,
so get out.

572
00:33:03,550 --> 00:33:05,790
I'm too worried to go to sleep.

573
00:33:14,700 --> 00:33:17,700
(Cheongpo Terminal)

574
00:33:17,770 --> 00:33:21,700
(Cheongpo Motel)

575
00:33:29,180 --> 00:33:31,150
(Saebit Employment Agency)

576
00:34:00,540 --> 00:34:03,380
Is he possessed by a ghost
who died from being unable...

577
00:34:04,210 --> 00:34:05,920
to work much?

578
00:34:06,620 --> 00:34:08,580
He'll be too tired to work tomorrow.

579
00:34:10,950 --> 00:34:12,090
Young man!

580
00:34:12,690 --> 00:34:13,860
What's your last name?

581
00:34:28,040 --> 00:34:29,710
(5:05 a.m.)

582
00:34:33,140 --> 00:34:34,710
(Flash Logistics Center)

583
00:34:34,780 --> 00:34:36,250
(Flash Logistics Center)

584
00:34:36,380 --> 00:34:38,050
(Flash Logistics Center)

585
00:34:40,050 --> 00:34:42,250
Didn't you sleep last night?

586
00:34:42,390 --> 00:34:43,550
Your face looks lifeless.

587
00:34:43,850 --> 00:34:45,190
What kind of work can I do today?

588
00:34:48,020 --> 00:34:49,060
That's 3.82.

589
00:34:59,440 --> 00:35:01,940
Mr. Park, should I order
a packed lunch today as well?

590
00:35:01,940 --> 00:35:02,940
Yes.

591
00:35:02,940 --> 00:35:04,070
(Chief Director Park Seong Jae)

592
00:35:04,070 --> 00:35:05,780
Coffee too, please.

593
00:35:09,850 --> 00:35:10,880
Ji Hyuk,

594
00:35:11,580 --> 00:35:13,820
you'll come back
when it's time, right?

595
00:35:19,990 --> 00:35:22,330
(Ji Hyuk, you'll come back
when it's time, right?)

596
00:35:22,430 --> 00:35:26,000
(Flash Logistics Center)

597
00:35:34,040 --> 00:35:38,670
(Yes)

598
00:35:50,220 --> 00:35:52,150
(Jung Hyeon Su Architecture Lab)

599
00:35:56,060 --> 00:35:57,930
(Cafe Agit, Part-timer wanted)

600
00:36:05,400 --> 00:36:08,000
He should be taking breaks.
Look at him.

601
00:36:09,910 --> 00:36:10,940
Goodness.

602
00:36:11,210 --> 00:36:13,540
- He should take a break.
- He never does.

603
00:36:13,540 --> 00:36:15,280
- He'll pass out at this rate.
- Tell me about it.

604
00:36:15,280 --> 00:36:16,580
This might put him in the hospital.

605
00:36:16,580 --> 00:36:18,810
- Can you believe it?
- How can he keep working like that?

606
00:36:18,810 --> 00:36:20,950
(Flash Logistics Center)

607
00:36:43,170 --> 00:36:44,240
Unbelievable.

608
00:36:44,770 --> 00:36:46,540
He's a quiet one, isn't he?

609
00:36:49,350 --> 00:36:51,310
We've been working together
for some time now,

610
00:36:51,310 --> 00:36:52,380
so let me pour you some makgeolli.

611
00:36:55,420 --> 00:36:56,450
I'm good.

612
00:36:57,850 --> 00:36:58,850
Look here, Lee.

613
00:36:59,590 --> 00:37:01,560
You're making
people uncomfortable...

614
00:37:01,620 --> 00:37:03,390
by distancing yourself like that.

615
00:37:09,930 --> 00:37:12,500
You don't need to say anything
for me to know how you feel.

616
00:37:20,380 --> 00:37:21,640
Goodness.

617
00:37:35,390 --> 00:37:37,360
- What?
- Oh, dear. Lee!

618
00:37:37,430 --> 00:37:38,490
- Goodness.
- Lee?

619
00:37:38,490 --> 00:37:39,600
- Lee?
- Lee!

620
00:37:40,560 --> 00:37:43,730
I don't see what Ji Hyuk
likes so much about this.

621
00:37:53,440 --> 00:37:54,610
(Lee Ji Hyuk)

622
00:37:57,050 --> 00:37:58,050
Hey, Ji Hyuk.

623
00:37:58,380 --> 00:37:59,380
Hello?

624
00:38:00,120 --> 00:38:01,850
Actually, I'm not Lee Ji Hyuk.

625
00:38:10,730 --> 00:38:12,800
Did he just fall asleep?

626
00:38:12,800 --> 00:38:13,960
Yes.

627
00:38:13,960 --> 00:38:16,730
We all thought
he was having a heart attack,

628
00:38:17,300 --> 00:38:19,540
but he started snoring
in the ambulance.

629
00:38:21,140 --> 00:38:22,610
The doctor says...

630
00:38:22,610 --> 00:38:24,540
he probably hasn't slept
in 4 or 5 days.

631
00:38:24,840 --> 00:38:27,010
That's why he passed out right away
after having some makgeolli.

632
00:38:29,550 --> 00:38:31,380
Thank you for taking care of him.

633
00:38:31,910 --> 00:38:34,480
I called you because yours was
the last number on his phone.

634
00:38:37,020 --> 00:38:38,020
Thank you.

635
00:38:39,060 --> 00:38:40,190
Anyway, once he wakes up,

636
00:38:40,820 --> 00:38:43,330
please tell him
that Song wants to see him tomorrow.

637
00:38:43,790 --> 00:38:45,700
- Okay. Get back safely.
- All right.

638
00:38:57,070 --> 00:38:58,240
Ji Hyuk.

639
00:39:00,810 --> 00:39:02,040
Open your eyes now.

640
00:39:04,280 --> 00:39:06,720
If you were me,
would you want to open them?

641
00:39:06,720 --> 00:39:07,780
You crazy fool.

642
00:39:08,280 --> 00:39:10,120
Then you should've turned off
your phone.

643
00:39:10,990 --> 00:39:12,660
Oh, dear.

644
00:39:15,960 --> 00:39:18,160
I can't keep my phone off.
I need to take calls from work.

645
00:39:21,130 --> 00:39:22,470
Let's go eat something.

646
00:39:23,530 --> 00:39:24,770
The IV is finished.

647
00:39:47,990 --> 00:39:49,530
How long are you going to stay here?

648
00:39:50,730 --> 00:39:52,800
Are you asking me
because you expect me to answer?

649
00:39:57,630 --> 00:39:59,470
You'll come back
when you hear from the company...

650
00:39:59,900 --> 00:40:01,100
you applied to, won't you?

651
00:40:12,310 --> 00:40:13,650
Why have you lost so much weight?

652
00:40:15,820 --> 00:40:17,290
Eating alone is no fun.

653
00:40:23,460 --> 00:40:24,490
Are you done?

654
00:40:30,470 --> 00:40:31,500
Let's go.

655
00:40:46,650 --> 00:40:49,390
(Charcoal-grilled dakgalbi,
makguksu)

656
00:40:50,650 --> 00:40:51,750
I'll get going, Ji Hyuk.

657
00:40:53,360 --> 00:40:54,390
Bye.

658
00:40:55,990 --> 00:40:57,690
I won't tell your parents anything.

659
00:40:59,160 --> 00:41:00,230
Of course, you shouldn't.

660
00:41:17,450 --> 00:41:19,050
I just can't leave like this.

661
00:41:19,620 --> 00:41:21,050
How long are you going to stay here?

662
00:41:21,780 --> 00:41:23,690
Do you know how worried
your family is about you?

663
00:41:27,820 --> 00:41:30,730
It's no use
crying over spilled milk.

664
00:41:30,890 --> 00:41:32,030
Even if you're here,

665
00:41:32,030 --> 00:41:34,260
what happened in Seoul
stays there. You know that.

666
00:41:35,100 --> 00:41:36,830
Even if it's hard,
you have to face it.

667
00:41:39,700 --> 00:41:40,770
And...

668
00:41:42,540 --> 00:41:44,510
why are you
beating yourself up so hard?

669
00:41:45,310 --> 00:41:47,640
It's Jung Bo A's fault,
and you are the victim.

670
00:41:49,250 --> 00:41:50,280
That's enough.

671
00:41:51,510 --> 00:41:52,650
I know what I'm doing.

672
00:41:57,950 --> 00:41:58,990
Ji Hyuk.

673
00:42:00,360 --> 00:42:01,560
Just go back with me.

674
00:42:02,060 --> 00:42:03,430
Let's go, Ji Hyuk.

675
00:42:09,870 --> 00:42:10,930
Take care.

676
00:42:14,300 --> 00:42:16,270
(Charcoal-grilled dakgalbi,
makguksu)

677
00:42:36,860 --> 00:42:38,930
That jerk abandoned me.

678
00:42:40,000 --> 00:42:42,630
"You'll stay in hiding for a while,
and when everyone is tired,"

679
00:42:43,530 --> 00:42:46,400
"you will come back
and find a job somewhere again."

680
00:42:47,800 --> 00:42:51,040
This is what you're thinking,
Park Seong Jae.

681
00:43:03,320 --> 00:43:04,320
(1,000 dollars)

682
00:43:05,790 --> 00:43:07,620
Park Seong Jae, you jerk...

683
00:43:31,280 --> 00:43:32,550
Good night, Mom.

684
00:43:35,220 --> 00:43:36,290
Sit.

685
00:43:38,950 --> 00:43:39,990
What's the matter?

686
00:43:40,620 --> 00:43:44,260
About the wedding
you attended the other day.

687
00:43:44,960 --> 00:43:46,330
Was it the senior's wedding?

688
00:43:47,060 --> 00:43:48,460
What senior?

689
00:43:49,030 --> 00:43:51,170
You know who I'm talking about.

690
00:43:51,470 --> 00:43:54,570
I'm talking about Lee, the guy
you've always had feelings for.

691
00:43:55,600 --> 00:43:57,140
Did I tell you...

692
00:43:57,370 --> 00:43:59,040
that it was Ji Hyuk's wedding?

693
00:44:02,980 --> 00:44:05,450
Do you want me
to arrange a blind date for you?

694
00:44:06,420 --> 00:44:07,450
A blind date?

695
00:44:07,450 --> 00:44:10,250
Yes. You know, there's a bank
behind my restaurant.

696
00:44:10,250 --> 00:44:13,590
Three men from the bank
are regulars at my restaurant.

697
00:44:14,620 --> 00:44:16,460
They are nice-looking, friendly,

698
00:44:16,460 --> 00:44:17,860
and eat well.

699
00:44:17,860 --> 00:44:19,430
I really like them.

700
00:44:19,430 --> 00:44:22,130
My gosh. Don't be ridiculous.

701
00:44:23,070 --> 00:44:24,100
Hey.

702
00:44:24,700 --> 00:44:27,500
Having a crush on someone
for a long time isn't easy.

703
00:44:28,600 --> 00:44:32,140
It is easier to get over someone
by seeing someone else.

704
00:44:33,310 --> 00:44:35,340
Mom, it's not what you think.

705
00:44:37,280 --> 00:44:39,950
It seems like
you've had a crush on him...

706
00:44:39,950 --> 00:44:41,850
for several years.

707
00:44:42,750 --> 00:44:45,050
And yet, you two
didn't end up together.

708
00:44:45,590 --> 00:44:47,590
That means you two
aren't meant to be together.

709
00:44:51,190 --> 00:44:54,260
Still, it has been
quite a long time.

710
00:44:55,100 --> 00:44:58,070
I can imagine how heartbroken
you must be right now.

711
00:45:02,600 --> 00:45:06,180
My goodness. Look at you.

712
00:45:06,940 --> 00:45:08,940
Stop it.
Why are you being like this, Mom?

713
00:45:08,940 --> 00:45:10,480
I'm not crying because I'm sad.

714
00:45:11,080 --> 00:45:12,280
I know.

715
00:45:12,710 --> 00:45:14,950
You are crying
because you can't get over him.

716
00:45:15,080 --> 00:45:16,290
Darn it.

717
00:45:17,720 --> 00:45:18,890
Still,

718
00:45:19,720 --> 00:45:21,460
I don't need you
to set me up on a blind date.

719
00:45:22,160 --> 00:45:24,890
(Seonsim Hospital)

720
00:45:28,230 --> 00:45:31,800
Yeong Ra, this isn't something
you should be so stubborn about.

721
00:45:32,200 --> 00:45:33,540
You have no idea...

722
00:45:34,470 --> 00:45:36,040
how terrified I was.

723
00:45:39,040 --> 00:45:41,580
Not just anyone
can enter this VIP room.

724
00:45:42,180 --> 00:45:44,750
I'll stay here
until we get a new driver.

725
00:45:46,880 --> 00:45:49,550
I said I'd drive you
and pick you up.

726
00:45:50,020 --> 00:45:52,390
How are you going to protect me?

727
00:45:53,390 --> 00:45:55,890
So, I told you to use my driver.

728
00:45:56,060 --> 00:45:59,360
Honey, that's the last thing
I want to do.

729
00:45:59,800 --> 00:46:02,530
I hate it when you don't separate
personal matters from business.

730
00:46:03,030 --> 00:46:06,030
That just ruins
your reputation at work.

731
00:46:06,340 --> 00:46:08,070
Using the company driver
for personal use.

732
00:46:09,100 --> 00:46:11,240
Then, as Yeong Ra says,

733
00:46:11,240 --> 00:46:13,810
we should keep her here
until we find a new driver.

734
00:46:13,910 --> 00:46:15,840
That's not a good idea.

735
00:46:16,450 --> 00:46:19,280
She has already wasted
a lot of time in the hospital.

736
00:46:20,280 --> 00:46:22,780
She can't waste more time
before the exhibition.

737
00:46:24,020 --> 00:46:25,690
I'll drive her around.

738
00:46:25,750 --> 00:46:27,390
You could be in danger too.

739
00:46:27,890 --> 00:46:29,890
He intentionally hurt Mr. Jung...

740
00:46:29,890 --> 00:46:32,330
and tried to kidnap Yeong Ra.

741
00:46:34,460 --> 00:46:35,760
Seong Jae.

742
00:46:37,870 --> 00:46:38,930
Hey.

743
00:46:40,470 --> 00:46:42,040
I'm glad you're here.

744
00:46:42,040 --> 00:46:43,770
I need you to make a wise decision,
like Solomon's judgment.

745
00:46:44,970 --> 00:46:45,970
Solomon?

746
00:46:46,610 --> 00:46:49,610
Yeong Ra has to be back
at her art studio starting tomorrow,

747
00:46:49,850 --> 00:46:51,510
and I was going to take her.

748
00:46:51,850 --> 00:46:53,150
However, your father suggested...

749
00:46:53,150 --> 00:46:54,950
that the company chauffeur
drive her,

750
00:46:54,950 --> 00:46:56,720
which is considered personal use.

751
00:46:56,790 --> 00:46:58,020
You have to admit that's wrong.

752
00:46:59,290 --> 00:47:01,390
Haven't you been able
to hire a new driver for her?

753
00:47:01,660 --> 00:47:03,090
There are a few candidates,

754
00:47:03,930 --> 00:47:06,090
but one of them
could be the stalker.

755
00:47:07,460 --> 00:47:09,460
Since we're terrified,

756
00:47:09,930 --> 00:47:12,570
we want to hire someone
after a thorough background check.

757
00:47:12,600 --> 00:47:15,370
It's a shame that every applicant
seems to have shortcomings.

758
00:47:17,170 --> 00:47:20,810
Why don't I take care of her
for the time being?

759
00:47:22,010 --> 00:47:23,010
You?

760
00:47:23,950 --> 00:47:26,850
You must be busy with your own work.

761
00:47:27,380 --> 00:47:28,620
We have no choice.

762
00:47:28,820 --> 00:47:30,220
I'll look for someone
within my circle.

763
00:47:31,820 --> 00:47:32,850
Sure.

764
00:47:33,260 --> 00:47:34,420
Thanks, Seong Jae.

765
00:47:49,300 --> 00:47:51,210
What kind of favor made you come...

766
00:47:51,340 --> 00:47:52,570
all the way here
instead of just calling me?

767
00:47:57,480 --> 00:47:59,450
Did something happen
to your parents?

768
00:47:59,550 --> 00:48:00,550
No.

769
00:48:01,750 --> 00:48:02,920
It's for me, actually.

770
00:48:03,590 --> 00:48:04,650
My gosh.

771
00:48:05,250 --> 00:48:06,390
What do you need?

772
00:48:07,160 --> 00:48:09,260
Seong Jae, can you appear
on my YouTube channel?

773
00:48:09,260 --> 00:48:10,960
I'll make sure
your face doesn't show.

774
00:48:11,960 --> 00:48:13,760
You know what?

775
00:48:14,760 --> 00:48:17,000
Drink my coffee too
and get home safely.

776
00:48:17,030 --> 00:48:18,070
Hold on.

777
00:48:18,730 --> 00:48:21,940
You can't leave
without hearing me out.

778
00:48:22,040 --> 00:48:23,710
You should ask a favor
from someone...

779
00:48:23,710 --> 00:48:25,640
who can actually say yes.

780
00:48:25,640 --> 00:48:26,940
I hate doing things like that.

781
00:48:27,540 --> 00:48:29,810
I'm putting together
a boyfriend wardrobe,

782
00:48:29,880 --> 00:48:31,480
and you're my best pick to model it.

783
00:48:31,480 --> 00:48:32,650
A wardrobe for boyfriends?

784
00:48:35,050 --> 00:48:36,720
Su Bin,
you're not thinking straight.

785
00:48:37,190 --> 00:48:39,620
There must be a lot of men
in their 20s around you.

786
00:48:39,620 --> 00:48:41,690
I chose you for a reason.

787
00:48:41,690 --> 00:48:42,720
I won't do it.

788
00:48:42,820 --> 00:48:43,830
Come on.

789
00:48:44,160 --> 00:48:45,630
How could you?

790
00:48:48,930 --> 00:48:50,500
If you cared about my parents,

791
00:48:51,770 --> 00:48:53,040
you wouldn't say no.

792
00:48:54,070 --> 00:48:55,170
How could you?

793
00:48:59,470 --> 00:49:00,780
Unbelievable.

794
00:49:03,280 --> 00:49:05,850
By the way, how are your parents?

795
00:49:06,980 --> 00:49:08,350
As if I need to spell it out.

796
00:49:08,920 --> 00:49:11,650
I really need to make it now
and save my family from drowning.

797
00:49:12,750 --> 00:49:13,860
Darn.

798
00:49:14,660 --> 00:49:16,090
Ji Hyuk's gone,

799
00:49:16,460 --> 00:49:18,230
Dad's job offer was canceled,

800
00:49:18,860 --> 00:49:20,360
and Ji Wan's out of a job.

801
00:49:21,800 --> 00:49:22,800
Why's Ji Wan out of a job?

802
00:49:23,330 --> 00:49:24,700
Did he quit?

803
00:49:24,870 --> 00:49:25,870
Yes.

804
00:49:27,570 --> 00:49:28,670
It's been a while.

805
00:49:30,040 --> 00:49:31,110
But...

806
00:49:31,610 --> 00:49:33,140
Mom and Dad don't know yet.

807
00:49:34,440 --> 00:49:36,780
This is the situation
my family's in, Seong Jae.

808
00:49:41,320 --> 00:49:42,420
Just this once.

809
00:49:45,720 --> 00:49:47,290
Hey, Seong Jae. What's up?

810
00:49:47,420 --> 00:49:48,860
I heard you quit your job.

811
00:49:50,290 --> 00:49:51,460
Can we meet up?

812
00:50:14,750 --> 00:50:16,320
Unbelievable.

813
00:50:17,290 --> 00:50:21,060
(March 2023)

814
00:50:24,690 --> 00:50:25,830
This isn't bad.

815
00:50:28,160 --> 00:50:30,070
Why did you toss this out
when it's actually good?

816
00:50:31,030 --> 00:50:32,070
Well...

817
00:50:33,240 --> 00:50:36,340
Ji Hyuk, don't say
useless things like that.

818
00:50:37,510 --> 00:50:38,570
That's it, Ji Eun Oh.

819
00:50:38,940 --> 00:50:40,180
You know your place, don't you?

820
00:50:41,110 --> 00:50:43,380
Here I was, worrying you might think
it's actually good.

821
00:50:47,450 --> 00:50:48,620
Leave if you're only going
to tease me.

822
00:50:56,120 --> 00:50:57,330
This will help.

823
00:50:59,800 --> 00:51:01,360
What's this?

824
00:51:16,380 --> 00:51:17,410
Ji Hyuk...

825
00:51:20,320 --> 00:51:21,350
Keep at it.

826
00:51:37,530 --> 00:51:38,530
Strike that.

827
00:51:39,400 --> 00:51:40,470
You're going to do well.

828
00:51:41,700 --> 00:51:43,140
You're that strong
when you apply yourself to things.

829
00:52:11,130 --> 00:52:12,370
This is a problem.

830
00:52:17,510 --> 00:52:19,610
(Colored pencils)

831
00:52:19,610 --> 00:52:20,780
(Colored pencils)

832
00:52:22,080 --> 00:52:23,080
Excuse me.

833
00:52:23,080 --> 00:52:24,480
I heard you did interior design.

834
00:52:25,010 --> 00:52:26,410
Yes, that's right.

835
00:52:26,880 --> 00:52:28,650
Does that include studio apartments?
How much would that cost?

836
00:52:28,880 --> 00:52:30,590
Can you email me...

837
00:52:30,590 --> 00:52:32,090
the floor plan and budget?

838
00:52:32,090 --> 00:52:33,720
I can't do a consultation right now.

839
00:52:33,860 --> 00:52:34,890
Let me give you my business card.

840
00:52:36,090 --> 00:52:38,690
I don't need your service right now.
I was just curious.

841
00:52:39,790 --> 00:52:41,760
- Have a good day.
- Bye.

842
00:52:47,570 --> 00:52:48,570
What is it?

843
00:52:49,170 --> 00:52:51,240
I hadn't realized it
while working on other things,

844
00:52:51,410 --> 00:52:52,610
but more customers...

845
00:52:52,610 --> 00:52:54,880
have started stopping by
to watch what I'm doing.

846
00:52:55,440 --> 00:52:56,580
You must feel interrupted.

847
00:52:57,050 --> 00:52:58,580
That must be tough
for the Queen of Focus.

848
00:52:59,380 --> 00:53:02,580
I should raise the screen
as a partition.

849
00:53:02,880 --> 00:53:03,920
Yes.

850
00:53:05,420 --> 00:53:07,920
That solves your problem,

851
00:53:08,390 --> 00:53:09,820
so I'm off to solve mine.

852
00:53:11,090 --> 00:53:12,330
Is there an issue you must handle?

853
00:53:12,530 --> 00:53:13,600
Yes, my hair.

854
00:53:15,530 --> 00:53:17,330
I told you
I was going on a blind date.

855
00:53:17,330 --> 00:53:18,630
I booked
a hair coloring appointment.

856
00:53:21,070 --> 00:53:22,870
- What about me?
- What about you?

857
00:53:23,170 --> 00:53:24,740
I want to go on a blind date too.

858
00:53:25,810 --> 00:53:26,810
Really?

859
00:53:27,310 --> 00:53:28,310
For real?

860
00:53:29,010 --> 00:53:31,080
I was waiting for you
to ask me first.

861
00:53:31,280 --> 00:53:33,950
Su Jeong, why won't you
set me up with anyone?

862
00:53:34,120 --> 00:53:36,280
Hey. Seriously.

863
00:53:37,020 --> 00:53:38,850
You're a funny one.

864
00:53:39,820 --> 00:53:41,490
Tell me. What's gotten into you?

865
00:53:43,560 --> 00:53:44,560
My mom, actually.

866
00:53:45,560 --> 00:53:47,730
Nice. Let's go as far as we can.

867
00:53:48,460 --> 00:53:51,070
Hey, let's come up
with a detailed plan.

868
00:53:51,070 --> 00:53:53,200
- How so?
- I'll put together...

869
00:53:53,200 --> 00:53:55,600
a list of about 17 guys,

870
00:53:55,600 --> 00:53:56,640
so sift through them.

871
00:53:56,910 --> 00:53:59,170
Do you have that many male friends?

872
00:53:59,510 --> 00:54:00,510
Goodness.

873
00:54:00,680 --> 00:54:02,880
I might've made more friends
if I hadn't always been stuck...

874
00:54:02,880 --> 00:54:04,450
at the cafe because of you.

875
00:54:08,120 --> 00:54:10,150
It is easier to get over someone...

876
00:54:10,150 --> 00:54:11,520
by seeing someone else.

877
00:54:12,390 --> 00:54:14,390
Why sift through them
when I can meet them all?

878
00:54:14,520 --> 00:54:17,360
Until construction starts,
I'll see two guys a week.

879
00:54:17,460 --> 00:54:18,560
- Really?
- Yes.

880
00:54:21,000 --> 00:54:22,030
What is it?

881
00:54:22,330 --> 00:54:24,500
He looked a lot like
Director Seong Jae.

882
00:54:27,300 --> 00:54:30,570
What do you think he does
when he's bored and not at the cafe?

883
00:54:31,570 --> 00:54:32,570
Unbelievable.

884
00:54:33,380 --> 00:54:35,540
It took you long enough
to show concern.

885
00:54:36,080 --> 00:54:38,080
He used to stop by for coffee
on his way to work,

886
00:54:38,080 --> 00:54:40,220
spend an hour at the cafe
during his lunch break,

887
00:54:40,420 --> 00:54:42,250
and even come on Saturdays to read,

888
00:54:42,520 --> 00:54:44,590
but he hasn't been around in weeks.

889
00:54:46,590 --> 00:54:47,720
Now, I feel guilty.

890
00:54:50,090 --> 00:54:51,830
Seong Jae,
I've been curious about something.

891
00:54:52,260 --> 00:54:53,330
Can I ask you a question?

892
00:54:53,330 --> 00:54:54,400
(July 2016)

893
00:54:54,400 --> 00:54:56,230
- Sure.
- Why do you...

894
00:54:56,230 --> 00:54:57,700
always say you're bored?

895
00:54:58,600 --> 00:55:00,040
Because I don't have a girlfriend.

896
00:55:01,200 --> 00:55:03,070
Look at you.

897
00:55:03,440 --> 00:55:05,510
You're sweet, tall, and handsome.

898
00:55:05,870 --> 00:55:07,410
So why are you always single?

899
00:55:07,740 --> 00:55:10,080
I'm not sure.
Is it because I'm too kind?

900
00:55:10,280 --> 00:55:11,380
Careful!

901
00:55:13,210 --> 00:55:15,320
Seong Jae was born to be bored.

902
00:55:15,720 --> 00:55:16,920
Not having hobbies is his hobby.

903
00:55:17,020 --> 00:55:18,720
- Here.
- He's right.

904
00:55:18,750 --> 00:55:20,290
If you don't let me
hang out with you,

905
00:55:20,890 --> 00:55:22,420
I'll return to the US...

906
00:55:22,420 --> 00:55:23,630
after being bored
during my school break.

907
00:55:23,660 --> 00:55:24,660
Eun Oh, mind your head.

908
00:55:25,260 --> 00:55:26,260
(Value of Hangyeol)

909
00:55:27,600 --> 00:55:28,730
Now, I feel bad for you.

910
00:55:29,430 --> 00:55:32,400
You know what?
Come over all the time, Seong Jae.

911
00:55:33,670 --> 00:55:35,500
Can I really come by all the time?

912
00:55:36,740 --> 00:55:37,740
Hey.

913
00:55:38,340 --> 00:55:40,340
I was actually quite surprised
by your attitude.

914
00:55:40,910 --> 00:55:42,780
Considering the years
you've known each other,

915
00:55:42,780 --> 00:55:43,950
wouldn't that make you friends?

916
00:55:44,350 --> 00:55:46,820
Have you only considered him
as a friend of Ji Hyuk's?

917
00:55:48,620 --> 00:55:51,590
Of course not. That's not the case.

918
00:55:52,320 --> 00:55:54,360
Then why have you not cared?

919
00:55:57,660 --> 00:55:58,660
What?

920
00:55:59,530 --> 00:56:00,530
What is it?

921
00:56:00,560 --> 00:56:02,160
- It's been a while.
- Hey.

922
00:56:02,530 --> 00:56:04,100
- How long has it been?
- Good for you.

923
00:56:05,370 --> 00:56:06,530
Here we go.

924
00:56:06,700 --> 00:56:08,540
- The van's here.
- Let's go.

925
00:56:10,270 --> 00:56:12,270
- Hello.
- Hello.

926
00:56:12,540 --> 00:56:13,710
- Hello.
- Goodness.

927
00:56:14,440 --> 00:56:15,480
- You.
- Right.

928
00:56:15,480 --> 00:56:17,010
- You.
- Thank you.

929
00:56:17,150 --> 00:56:18,180
You over there!

930
00:56:18,680 --> 00:56:20,180
- Get in, please.
- Goodness.

931
00:56:20,180 --> 00:56:21,320
Go on.

932
00:56:21,350 --> 00:56:22,620
- Darn.
- Let's go!

933
00:56:22,750 --> 00:56:24,020
Come on, guys.

934
00:56:24,020 --> 00:56:25,050
Hurry over here.

935
00:56:37,530 --> 00:56:39,570
- I see you're out here, Director.
- Welcome.

936
00:56:39,800 --> 00:56:41,440
I thought
three people would do today.

937
00:56:41,440 --> 00:56:42,640
- Sure.
- Hello.

938
00:56:43,170 --> 00:56:44,670
We need to repair the collapsed wall
behind the building,

939
00:56:45,010 --> 00:56:46,740
but too many weeds are in our way.

940
00:56:46,740 --> 00:56:48,680
You only need
to pull out weeds today.

941
00:56:48,680 --> 00:56:49,710
That's right.

942
00:56:50,480 --> 00:56:52,810
Hi, what's your name?

943
00:56:56,420 --> 00:56:57,750
(Edel Orphanage)

944
00:57:14,670 --> 00:57:16,100
They're hard workers.

945
00:57:16,100 --> 00:57:17,210
Please do a good job today.

946
00:57:17,670 --> 00:57:18,670
I'm sorry,

947
00:57:19,410 --> 00:57:20,540
but I have to go.

948
00:57:23,240 --> 00:57:24,480
Is this a joke?

949
00:57:25,350 --> 00:57:26,850
You can't line up for a job...

950
00:57:27,150 --> 00:57:29,150
only to quit
once you get to the site.

951
00:57:29,550 --> 00:57:31,490
I have a bad back.

952
00:57:31,550 --> 00:57:32,620
Hey!

953
00:57:33,090 --> 00:57:34,490
Can you drive?

954
00:57:37,160 --> 00:57:38,160
Yes.

955
00:57:38,160 --> 00:57:39,430
Then, I'd like a favor.

956
00:57:40,200 --> 00:57:41,430
We have to go to Seoul...

957
00:57:41,430 --> 00:57:43,500
to get the glass we need
for this place,

958
00:57:43,500 --> 00:57:46,030
but our Mr. Kim sprained his ankle.

959
00:57:46,970 --> 00:57:48,300
Seoul?

960
00:57:48,300 --> 00:57:51,540
It's for the kids,
so could you do it?

961
00:57:51,640 --> 00:57:53,440
You're getting an easy day of work.

962
00:58:04,090 --> 00:58:06,920
Please take a right 100m ahead,
toward Seoul.

963
00:58:15,700 --> 00:58:17,670
(Seoul, Cheongpo)

964
00:58:29,510 --> 00:58:30,980
Come to the store when I call.

965
00:58:31,110 --> 00:58:32,110
Sure.

966
00:58:40,360 --> 00:58:41,390
I'm done here.

967
00:58:42,190 --> 00:58:43,420
Right, I'll soon be back.

968
00:58:45,130 --> 00:58:46,330
Really?

969
00:58:49,800 --> 00:58:51,100
Good for you.

970
00:58:54,070 --> 00:58:56,240
Of course, I got it.
Don't you know who I am?

971
00:58:56,240 --> 00:58:58,910
It was right there,
like it had been waiting for me.

972
00:59:05,750 --> 00:59:07,520
Sure, I'll be back soon.

973
00:59:39,380 --> 00:59:40,820
Hi, sir.

974
00:59:59,930 --> 01:00:02,140
Of course, I got it.
Don't you know who I am?

975
01:00:02,140 --> 01:00:04,470
It was right there,
like it had been waiting for me.

976
01:00:07,410 --> 01:00:08,810
You fool.

977
01:00:10,780 --> 01:00:12,980
What? What did you just say?

978
01:00:15,250 --> 01:00:16,350
What?

979
01:00:16,720 --> 01:00:18,650
I hurt my leg, that's all.

980
01:00:20,020 --> 01:00:21,590
Yes, I know that.

981
01:00:21,590 --> 01:00:23,420
So why would you call me a fool?

982
01:00:24,030 --> 01:00:25,590
That's not it.

983
01:00:28,130 --> 01:00:30,230
Someone just came to mind.

984
01:00:49,420 --> 01:00:51,490
You'll come back
when you hear from the company...

985
01:00:52,450 --> 01:00:53,520
you applied to, won't you?

986
01:00:59,990 --> 01:01:01,060
What a fool.

987
01:01:03,060 --> 01:01:04,330
Stop the truck.

988
01:01:05,170 --> 01:01:06,900
Stop the truck, you punk!

989
01:01:07,340 --> 01:01:09,470
- Stop the truck!
- Wait!

990
01:01:19,010 --> 01:01:21,720
What are you doing?

991
01:01:21,720 --> 01:01:22,850
Get out.

992
01:01:24,790 --> 01:01:26,090
What is this?

993
01:01:27,290 --> 01:01:30,060
Do you know how many times
you said "fool" on the way here?

994
01:01:30,220 --> 01:01:31,890
Over ten times!

995
01:01:31,890 --> 01:01:33,230
Yet you weren't talking about me?

996
01:01:33,730 --> 01:01:35,800
- Did I say that?
- You psycho!

997
01:01:37,470 --> 01:01:39,530
Darn you!

998
01:02:06,090 --> 01:02:07,260
I hate this.

999
01:02:20,340 --> 01:02:22,140
Sure. Have a good night.

1000
01:02:36,960 --> 01:02:38,530
Hey, Director.

1001
01:02:39,830 --> 01:02:40,930
Eun Oh.

1002
01:02:43,500 --> 01:02:44,500
What...

1003
01:02:47,200 --> 01:02:48,500
do you think of me?

1004
01:03:54,900 --> 01:03:57,710
(Our Golden Days)

1005
01:03:57,940 --> 01:04:00,640
I can work any job as long as
the paycheck keeps coming...

1006
01:04:00,640 --> 01:04:02,110
until our kids get married.

1007
01:04:02,110 --> 01:04:04,050
Since you're the one asking,

1008
01:04:04,050 --> 01:04:05,950
I'm glad to give you
two months of my time.

1009
01:04:05,950 --> 01:04:07,050
You need to ask your mom...

1010
01:04:07,050 --> 01:04:08,750
before you can tell me
your age? Why?

1011
01:04:08,750 --> 01:04:11,320
We've known each other
for nine years now.

1012
01:04:11,320 --> 01:04:14,190
I thought I was at least your friend
or an honorary senior.

1013
01:04:14,190 --> 01:04:15,660
Sure, Seong Jae.

1014
01:04:16,390 --> 01:04:18,560
Claim compensation.
It won't be chump change.

1015
01:04:18,560 --> 01:04:19,960
At 4 a.m. today,

1016
01:04:19,960 --> 01:04:21,730
the body of a man
in his early 30s...

1017
01:04:21,730 --> 01:04:23,660
was recovered
from Yangsu Reservoir...

1018
01:04:23,660 --> 01:04:25,030
I don't want to live like this.

1019
01:04:25,030 --> 01:04:26,770
I don't want my life
to be like this.

1020
01:04:27,240 --> 01:04:28,500
No!

1021
01:04:31,240 --> 01:04:33,240
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
